VPC Peering is a networking connection between two Virtual Private Clouds that allows them to communicate privately using internal IP addresses.
It avoids traffic going through the public internet.

Two VPCs request a peering connection.

The request is accepted by the other VPC owner.

Route tables are updated so each VPC knows how to reach the other network.

Resources (EC2, databases, etc.) communicate using private IP addresses.



**********************************************************************************************************************************************



1. create 2 vpc with different cidr block vpcA = 10.0.0.0/16 and vpcB = 10.1.0.0/16

2. create public and private subnets in both vpc

3. Go to VPC and select peering option select both the vpc and create it and then accept the peering connection from second vpc.

4. Go to vpcA public route table and edit routes --> add cidr range of vpcB e.g 10.1.0.0/16 and select peering connection.

5. Go to vpcB public route table and edit routes --> add cidr range of vpcB e.g 10.0.0.0/16 and select peering connection.

6. you can connect the private server of vpcB from public server of vpcA.
